Describe the biggest difference between .forEach & .map.
    .forEach doesn't make an array out of the returns of the function impemented in it.

What is the difference between a function and a method?
    Method is just a bit more complicated, in that it's a function value for a property.

What is closure?
    Anything that defines a particular section of code. Everything in a specific section of code's structure and anything refrencing it.

Describe the four rules of the 'this' keyword.
    1. This before a period is usually refering to the function parenting it.
    2. This can also call an object going to be made by a constructor. 
    3. This can reference a window when called alone.
    4. This can be called expliclitly in some cases such as .apply() and .call().

Why do we need super() in an extended class?
    We need super because it makes it easier to transfer the main classes methods, keys and values. You won't have to re-type the same code again and again and can save lots of time.